commit.message:
Use true SIMD v128.store for UTF-8→UTF-16 ASCII widening

Replace inline scalar byte writes with WASM SIMD i16x8.extend + v128.store:
@shuffle extracts low/high 8-byte halves, @intCast zero-extends u8→u16,
@bitCast + array store emits v128.store for 16-byte bulk writes.

Profiling confirms the bottleneck is JS object creation, not string
conversion — this change has minimal impact but is correct and clean.
